POLOKWANE Limpopo police have launched a manhunt for a group of suspects who attacked and killed a 35-year-old man on Thursday afternoon.READ: Limpopo police foil cash-in-transit heistPolice said the motive for the incident is unknown. It is alleged that a group of men chased the deceased until they caught him next to the rank at corner Buite and Devenish Streets, stripped him naked and started assaulting with sticks and stones, said Limpopo police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe.eNCA